  "subject": "Chore: Modernize docs configuration for Python 3.12+",
  "commit_message": "Chore: Modernize docs configuration for Python 3.12+\n\nRemove broken/outdated Python modules that are incompatible with modern\nPython versions. Replace lfdocs-conf dependency with standalone conf.py.\nUpdate .readthedocs.yaml to use ubuntu-24.04 and Python 3.13. Modernize\ntox.ini (use allowlist_externals, pin basepython to 3.12, use local\nconstraints). Remove obsolete docs/conf.yaml, root tox.ini, and legacy\ntemplates. Fix ribbon.css max-width per doc-rules. Add local copy of\netc/upper-constraints.onap.txt from the doc repo.\n\nReplace broken cross-project :ref: to vnf_requirements_documentation\nwith a direct URL to the RTD project, since intersphinx is not\nconfigured for vnfrqts/requirements and the -W flag now treats\nundefined labels as errors.\n\nRemoved modules: sphinxcontrib-swaggerdoc, sphinxcontrib-needs,\nsphinxcontrib-nwdiag, sphinx_bootstrap_theme, lfdocs-conf, tox, doc8,\nsix, Sphinx==1.8.1.\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nChange-Id: Iad6e67a99b34289148d08c84e4a654a462536394\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
